metadata.name: dim_products
metadata.comment: This table contains dimensional data for products across different categories, regions, and timeframes.  It provides aggregated insights into sales, returns, shipping, and revenue performance, along with key  customer satisfaction and operational metrics. The table is used in dashboards for product performance  analysis and sales strategy optimization.

date.name: date
date.comment: The date representing when the data for product performance was aggregated, providing a time reference for the metrics in the table.

country_id.name: country_id
country_id.comment: A unique identifier for each country in which the product is sold or marketed, used to join with other geographical data tables.

country.name: country
country.comment: The name of the country where the product is sold or marketed, used to filter product performance based on geographic regions.

product_category.name: product_category
product_category.comment: The category to which the product belongs, such as electronics, apparel, or digital assets, allowing for category-level analysis of performance.

product_name.name: product_name
product_name.comment: The name of the individual product being tracked, used for granular analysis of sales, returns, and other performance metrics.

nb_order_id.name: nb_order_id
nb_order_id.comment: The number of unique orders associated with the product, used to measure sales volume and demand for the product.

nb_shipping_id.name: nb_shipping_id
nb_shipping_id.comment: The number of shipping transactions associated with the product, used to track logistics performance and delivery efficiency.

nb_return_id.name: nb_return_id
nb_return_id.comment: The number of product returns, used to analyze product quality, customer satisfaction, and return rates for the product.

avg_fulfillment_days.name: avg_fulfillment_days
avg_fulfillment_days.comment: The average number of days it takes to fulfill an order for the product, providing insights into supply chain efficiency and customer experience.

avg_nps_score.name: avg_nps_score
avg_nps_score.comment: The average Net Promoter Score (NPS) for the product, indicating customer satisfaction and likelihood to recommend the product.

total_gross_revenue.name: total_gross_revenue
total_gross_revenue.comment: The total gross revenue generated by the product before any deductions for taxes, returns, or fees, providing a top-level view of sales performance.

total_tax_amount.name: total_tax_amount
total_tax_amount.comment: The total amount of taxes collected for sales of the product, used to calculate net revenue and assess the impact of taxes on overall profitability.

total_net_revenue_before_tax.name: total_net_revenue_before_tax
total_net_revenue_before_tax.comment: The total net revenue generated by the product before taxes are applied, used to assess profitability before accounting for tax obligations.

total_net_revenue_after_tax.name: total_net_revenue_after_tax
total_net_revenue_after_tax.comment: The total net revenue generated by the product after taxes have been deducted, providing an accurate representation of revenue after all tax liabilities.

total_cogs.name: total_cogs
total_cogs.comment: The total cost of goods sold (COGS) for the product, including manufacturing, shipping, and handling costs, used to calculate profit margins.

total_returned_cogs.name: total_returned_cogs
total_returned_cogs.comment: The total cost of goods sold for returned items, providing insights into the financial impact of product returns on profitability.

total_refund_amount.name: total_refund_amount
total_refund_amount.comment: The total amount refunded to customers for returned products, used to assess the overall impact of returns on net revenue.

total_payment_fee.name: total_payment_fee
total_payment_fee.comment: The total fees associated with payment processing for the product, including transaction fees from providers like credit card companies or digital wallets.

total_cm.name: total_cm
total_cm.comment: The total contribution margin for the product, calculated as net revenue minus cost of goods sold (COGS), providing a clear view of product profitability.

metadata.name: fct_orders
metadata.comment: Fact table capturing detailed information about customer orders, including order details, payment methods,  shipping, returns, and customer feedback. This table provides a comprehensive view of each order's lifecycle,  enabling in-depth analysis of sales performance, customer behavior, and product profitability.

country_id.name: country_id
country_id.comment: Identifier for the billing country of the order and used as the partition field.

country.name: country
country.comment: The billing country associated with the order.

order_status.name: order_status
order_status.comment:
Orders can be one of the following statuses:

| status         | description                                                               |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| completed      | The order has been placed and all payments were successful                |
| failed         | The order has been placed and at least one payment failed                 |

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.comment: Unique identifier for the customer placing the order.

nb_payments.name: nb_payments
nb_payments.comment: The number of payments made by the customer for the order.

first_name.name: first_name
first_name.comment: The first name of the customer.

last_name.name: last_name
last_name.comment: The last name of the customer.

is_shipped.name: is_shipped
is_shipped.comment: Indicates whether the order has been shipped (TRUE if shipped, FALSE otherwise).

shipping_id.name: shipping_id
shipping_id.comment: A unique identifier for each shipping transaction. This field ensures that each shipment is  tracked individually and is essential for linking sales orders to their corresponding shipping details.

shipping_amount.name: shipping_amount
shipping_amount.comment: The total gross amount charged for shipping the order.

payment_method.name: payment_method
payment_method.comment: The payment method used for the order; accepted values include 'amazon_pay', 'stripe', 'apple_pay', and 'bitcoin'.

gross_revenue.name: gross_revenue
gross_revenue.comment: The total gross amount paid by the customer, including tax and shipping.

tax_rate.name: tax_rate
tax_rate.comment: The tax rate applied to the order, based on the billing country.

tax_amount.name: tax_amount
tax_amount.comment: The total amount of tax charged on the order.

net_revenue_before_tax.name: net_revenue_before_tax
net_revenue_before_tax.comment: The gross revenue from the order minus the shipping amount.

net_revenue_after_tax.name: net_revenue_after_tax
net_revenue_after_tax.comment: The gross revenue from the order minus both shipping and tax amounts.

order_date.name: order_date
order_date.comment: The date on which the order was created.

shipping_date.name: shipping_date
shipping_date.comment: The date on which the order was shipped.

is_returned.name: is_returned
is_returned.comment: Indicates whether the order was returned (TRUE if returned, FALSE otherwise).

return_id.name: return_id
return_id.comment: A unique identifier for each return associated with an order. This field is populated only  if the order has been returned, and remains null for non-returned orders.

return_date.name: return_date
return_date.comment: The date on which the order was returned, if applicable.

return_reason.name: return_reason
return_reason.comment: The reason provided for returning the order, if applicable; accepted values include 'undersized', 'oversized', and 'defective'.

fulfillment_days.name: fulfillment_days
fulfillment_days.comment: The number of days between the order date and the shipping date, representing the time taken to fulfill the order.

is_nps.name: is_nps
is_nps.comment: Indicates whether the customer provided an NPS (Net Promoter Score) score (TRUE if provided, FALSE otherwise).

nps_score.name: nps_score
nps_score.comment: The Net Promoter Score (NPS) provided by the customer, ranging from 0 to 10, which indicates customer satisfaction and loyalty.

nps_date.name: nps_date
nps_date.comment: The date on which the customer provided their Net Promoter Score (NPS).

product_category_id.name: product_category_id
product_category_id.comment: Unique identifier for the product's category.

product_category.name: product_category
product_category.comment: The name of the category to which the product belongs.

cogs.name: cogs
cogs.comment: The cost of goods sold (COGS) for the product, representing the direct costs  attributable to the production of the product sold in the order.

returned_cogs.name: returned_cogs
returned_cogs.comment: The cost of goods sold (COGS) associated with returned products, representing  the direct costs of the returned items.

refund_amount.name: refund_amount
refund_amount.comment: The amount refunded to the customer for returned products or order cancellations.

payment_fee.name: payment_fee
payment_fee.comment: The fee charged by the payment processor for handling the transaction associated with the order.

cm.name: cm
cm.comment: The fee charged by the payment processor for handling the transaction associated with the order.

customer_order_nb.name: customer_order_nb
customer_order_nb.comment: The customer's order number. 1 indicates a first-time order (new customer), while any number  greater than 1 indicates that the customer has placed multiple orders (returning customer).

customer_type.name: customer_type
customer_type.comment: Indicates whether a customer is new or returning. The values can be 'new' for first-time  customers and 'returning' for customers who have made previous purchases.

metadata.name: fct_orders_timeseries_sma
metadata.comment: Fact table capturing the daily sales time series data, including the total net revenue after tax (`sales`).  The table also includes various Simple Moving Averages (SMA) and Bollinger Bands calculated over different  periods (14, 30, 60, 120, and 250 days). This table is essential for analyzing sales trends, understanding  market volatility, and smoothing out fluctuations in daily sales data."

date.name: date
date.comment: The date corresponding to the recorded sales figures.

sales.name: sales
sales.comment: The total net revenue after tax for each day, representing the sum of all sales transactions.  This field is used as the basis for calculating various metrics such as Simple Moving Averages (SMA) and Bollinger Bands.

sales_sma_14.name: sales_sma_14
sales_sma_14.comment: The 14-day Simple Moving Average (SMA) of daily sales, providing a balance between short-term and medium-term trend analysis.

sales_sma_30.name: sales_sma_30
sales_sma_30.comment: The 30-day Simple Moving Average (SMA) of daily sales, offering a slightly longer-term view on sales trends.

sales_sma_60.name: sales_sma_60
sales_sma_60.comment: The 60-day Simple Moving Average (SMA) of daily sales, representing a quarterly trend for sales data.

sales_sma_120.name: sales_sma_120
sales_sma_120.comment: The 120-day Simple Moving Average (SMA) of daily sales, useful for identifying trends over half a year.

sales_sma_250.name: sales_sma_250
sales_sma_250.comment: The 250-day Simple Moving Average (SMA) of daily sales, providing insights into yearly sales trends.

sales_stddev_14.name: sales_stddev_14
sales_stddev_14.comment: The 14-day standard deviation of daily sales, used to measure the volatility around the 14-day Simple Moving Average.

sales_stddev_30.name: sales_stddev_30
sales_stddev_30.comment: The 30-day standard deviation of daily sales, providing insights into the variability of sales around the 30-day Simple Moving Average.

sales_stddev_60.name: sales_stddev_60
sales_stddev_60.comment: The 60-day standard deviation of daily sales, indicating the volatility of sales trends over a quarterly period.

sales_stddev_120.name: sales_stddev_120
sales_stddev_120.comment: The 120-day standard deviation of daily sales, used to assess the variability of sales over approximately half a year.

sales_stddev_250.name: sales_stddev_250
sales_stddev_250.comment: The 250-day standard deviation of daily sales, reflecting the volatility around the annual sales trends.

sales_sma_upper_14.name: sales_sma_upper_14
sales_sma_upper_14.comment: The upper Bollinger Band for the 14-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA plus two standard deviations.  Indicates the potential upper bound of short-term sales trends.

sales_sma_lower_14.name: sales_sma_lower_14
sales_sma_lower_14.comment: The lower Bollinger Band for the 14-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA minus two standard deviations.  Indicates the potential lower bound of short-term sales trends.

sales_sma_upper_30.name: sales_sma_upper_30
sales_sma_upper_30.comment: The upper Bollinger Band for the 30-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA plus two standard deviations.  Represents the potential upper bound for monthly sales trends.

sales_sma_lower_30.name: sales_sma_lower_30
sales_sma_lower_30.comment: The lower Bollinger Band for the 30-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA minus two standard deviations.  Represents the potential lower bound for monthly sales trends.

sales_sma_upper_60.name: sales_sma_upper_60
sales_sma_upper_60.comment: The upper Bollinger Band for the 60-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA plus two standard deviations.  Indicates the upper limit of quarterly sales trends.

sales_sma_lower_60.name: sales_sma_lower_60
sales_sma_lower_60.comment: The lower Bollinger Band for the 60-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA minus two standard deviations.  Indicates the lower limit of quarterly sales trends.

sales_sma_upper_120.name: sales_sma_upper_120
sales_sma_upper_120.comment: The upper Bollinger Band for the 120-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA plus two standard deviations.  Provides the upper bound for sales trends over half a year.

sales_sma_lower_120.name: sales_sma_lower_120
sales_sma_lower_120.comment: The lower Bollinger Band for the 120-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA minus two standard deviations.  Provides the lower bound for sales trends over half a year.

sales_sma_upper_250.name: sales_sma_upper_250
sales_sma_upper_250.comment: The upper Bollinger Band for the 250-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA plus two standard deviations.  Used to gauge the upper limit of annual sales trends.

sales_sma_lower_250.name: sales_sma_lower_250
sales_sma_lower_250.comment: The lower Bollinger Band for the 250-day Simple Moving Average, calculated as the SMA minus two standard deviations.  Used to gauge the lower limit of annual sales trends.

metadata.name: fct_payment_methods
metadata.comment: Fact table containing details of payment methods used in customer orders.

country_id.name: country_id
country_id.comment: Identifier for the billing country associated with the order

country.name: country
country.comment: The name of the billing country associated with the order.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.comment: Unique identifier for the order, serving as a reference to the specific transaction.

nb_payments.name: nb_payments
nb_payments.comment: The total number of payments made for the order, indicating the frequency of transactions associated with the order.

payment_methods.name: payment_methods
payment_methods.comment: Indicates whether a single or multiple distinct payment methods were used for the order.  The value is 'single' if only one payment method was used or 'multiple' if more than one distinct payment method was utilized.

order_date.name: order_date
order_date.comment: The date on which the order was placed.

order_status.name: order_status
order_status.comment:
Orders can be one of the following statuses:

| status         | description                                                               |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| completed      | The order has been placed and all payments were successful                |
| failed         | The order has been placed and at least one payment failed                 |

total_gross_revenue.name: total_gross_revenue
total_gross_revenue.comment: The total gross revenue generated from the order, representing the sum of all payments before any deductions or fees.

total_payment_fees.name: total_payment_fees
total_payment_fees.comment: The total amount of fees incurred for processing all payment methods associated with the order.

amazon_pay_payment_fees.name: amazon_pay_payment_fees
amazon_pay_payment_fees.comment: The total fees charged for processing payments through Amazon Pay.

apple_pay_payment_fees.name: apple_pay_payment_fees
apple_pay_payment_fees.comment: The total fees charged for processing payments through Apple Pay.

bitcoin_payment_fees.name: bitcoin_payment_fees
bitcoin_payment_fees.comment: The total fees charged for processing payments through Bitcoin.

stripe_payment_fees.name: stripe_payment_fees
stripe_payment_fees.comment: The total fees charged for processing payments through Stripe.

amazon_pay_amount.name: amazon_pay_amount
amazon_pay_amount.comment: The total amount paid using Amazon Pay for the order.

apple_pay_amount.name: apple_pay_amount
apple_pay_amount.comment: The total amount paid using Apple Pay for the order.

bitcoin_amount.name: bitcoin_amount
bitcoin_amount.comment: The total amount paid using Bitcoin for the order.

stripe_amount.name: stripe_amount
stripe_amount.comment: The total amount paid using Stripe for the order.
